<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-913-192  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 913 192.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Nov 20 1989 v10 n46 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Metropolitan Fiber challenges local carrier monopolies.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Thyfault, Mary E.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Metropolitan Fiber Systems (MFS), a subsidiary of KiewitCommunications Co Inc, is going to court to force local-exchangecarriers (LEC) to unbundle their services so that other carrierscan offer local switched access services.andP;  Some observers havecompared the MFS suit to MCI's suit against the AT andamp; T monopoly,which resulted in the breakup of the Bell system.andP;  MCI broke upthe national telephone system, but local Bell companies continueto dominate their respective markets.andP;  These Bell operatingcompanies (BOCs) have kept access service prices artificially highand are collecting unlawful rates of return, according to the MFSsuit.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metropolitan Fiber Systems Inc. (cases).andO;Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesLaw SuitMonopolies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>